This paper discusses human-robot communication and knowledge representation, which are topics commonly found in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses natural language processing (cs.CL), which is a subfield of AI that deals with language understanding and generation. The use of Short Term Memory Buffers is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) to improve performance. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely to be associated with this paper.
